<item>
            <title>[LU-17571] Improve sanity.sh:test_77l,812a,812b,816</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17571</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity.sh:test_77l,812a,812b,816 rely on idle_timeout set to not 0. Otherwise they fail:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[root@vmcentos9-1 lus-10952]# lctl set_param osc.*.idle_timeout=0
osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff96c8daa30000.idle_timeout=0
osc.lustre-OST0001-osc-ffff96c8daa30000.idle_timeout=0
[root@vmcentos9-1 lus-10952]# ./sanity.sh 812a
vmcentos8-1: vmcentos8-1: executing check_logdir /tmp/test_logs/1708513331
..
== sanity test 812a: do not drop reqs generated when imp is going to idle (LU-11951) ========================================================== 14:02:33 (1708513353)
..
vmcentos9-1: executing wait_import_state CONNECTING osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff96c8daa30000.ost_server_uuid 50
 rpc test_812a: @@@@@@ FAIL: can&apos;t put import for osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff96c8daa30000.ost_server_uuid into CONNECTING state after 50 sec, have FULL
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These tests need to take care of idle_timeout.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
